---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <HeroSection 
      title="Terms & Conditions" 
      highlightText="Terms"
      description="Please read these terms and conditions thoroughly before using our service.\n Last updated: 8/20/2025"
    />
    
    <section class="py-12 ">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            Welcome to SnapSites. These Terms & Conditions govern your use of our website and services. By accessing or using our services, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
          </p>
          <br>
          
          <h2>2. Definitions</h2>
          <p>
            “Company,” “we,” “our,” or “us” refers to SnapSites LLC.<br>
            "Service" refers to the SnapSites platform and all related services.<br>
            "User" refers to any individual or entity that accesses or uses our Service.<br>
            "Content" refers to all information and materials available on our Service.
          </p>
          <br>
          
          <h2>3. Eligibility</h2>
          <p>
            You must be at least 18 years old and capable of entering into a legally binding agreement to use our Service. By subscribing, you confirm that the information you provide is accurate and complete.
          </p>
          <br>

          <h2>4. Services Provided</h2>
          <p>
            We provide website hosting, management, and support under a subscription model. The features included in your subscription are listed on our website and may change from time to time.
          </p>
          <br>

          <h2>5. Payment and Billing</h2>
          <p>
            Payments are processed securely through Stripe. We do not collect, store, or have access to your payment information. Subscription renews automatically at the end of each billing period unless cancelled. 
            You are responsible for ensuring that your payment method is valid and up to date.
          </p>
          <br>

          <h2>6. Automatic Renewal</h2>
          <p>
            Your subscription will automatically renew at the end of each billing cycle unless you cancel. By subscribing, you authorize us to charge your chosen payment method on a recurring basis until you cancel.
          </p>
          <br>

          <h2>7. Cancellation Policy</h2>
          <p>
            You may cancel your subscription at any time by contacting us. Upon cancellation, your Service will remain active until the end of your current billing period. No partial refunds are provided for unused time. 
            After the billing period ends, your website may be taken offline.
          </p>
          <br>

          <h2>8. Automatic Cancellation</h2>
          <p>
            If your payment method fails and you do not change it to a valid payment method within two weeks after your due date, the Service will be automatically and instantly cancelled. We have the right to take your website offline.
          </p>
          <br>

          <h2>9. Refund Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We do not provide refunds.
          </p>
          <br>

          <h2>10. Data Collection and Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            We do not sell, rent, or trade your data.
            We do not collect personal data beyond what you voluntarily provide through our contact form.
            The contact form may collect your name, email address, and any additional details you provide. This information is used solely for the purpose of contacting you and addressing the issue or request submitted.
            For payment processing, all personal and financial data is handled directly by Stripe in accordance with their policies.
          </p>
          <p>Read our <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a> to know what we collect on our website.</p>
          <br>

          <h2>11. Customer Responsibilities</h2>
          <p>
            You are responsible for ensuring that all content you provide (text, images, logos, etc.) is accurate, lawful, and does not infringe on the rights of others. You agree not to use our Service for illegal activities, spamming, or hosting prohibited content.
          </p>
          <br>

          <h2>12. Changes and Support</h2>
          <p>We provide email support and take requests and comments at snapsites4u@gmail.com</p>
          <p>Below is our classification of changes</p>
          <p>We classify requested changes as:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
            <li><p>Minor Changes: Work reasonably completed within one hour (e.g., text updates, image swaps, styling adjustments).</p></li>
            <li><p>Major Changes: Work requiring more than one hour or significantly altering design/functionality (e.g., new pages, integrations, redesigns).</p></li>
          </ul>
          <p>Upon submitting a change request to us, we classify it according to our definitions and we decide if the change is minor or major. The classification of a change as minor or major is at our sole discretion.</p>
          <br>

          <h2>13. Service Availability</h2>
          <p>
            We strive to provide reliable 24/7 service using industry-leading infrastructure. While we aim for continuous uptime, we do not guarantee uninterrupted access. 
            Occasional downtime may occur due to maintenance, provider issues, or circumstances beyond our control.
          </p>
          <br>

          <h2>14. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            All software, code, and design elements we provide remain our intellectual property. You retain ownership of any content you submit (text, images, logos, etc.). 
            We grant you the right to use the website during your active subscription to represent your business.
          </p>
          <br>

          <h2>15. Privacy Policy</h2>
